arguments.name: Connection
arguments.description: A text string of the name of the connection to the cube.

arguments.name: Set_expression
arguments.description: A text string of a set expression, such as "{[Item1].children}". Set_expression can also be the CUBESET function, or a reference to a cell that contains the CUBESET function.

arguments.name: Rank
arguments.description: An integer value specifying the top value to return. If rank is a value of 1, it returns the top value, if rank is a value of 2, it returns the second most top value, and so on. To return the top 5 values, use CUBERANKEDMEMBER five times, specifying a different rank, 1 through 5, each time.

arguments.name: Caption
arguments.description: A text string displayed in the cell instead of the caption, if one is defined, from the cube.
